Answer.Comments: This was the strangest survey and I'm not necessarily meaning the novel verbs. It seems that when I concentrated on the monster to determine what he was doing (in order to figure out the verb) I missed the "+" sign. Sometimes the videos were pixelated, more so toward the end. While it was interesting, I was glad to finish it! I definitely feel brain dead now.

Title: Merry Monster Survey
Description: Watch videos and answer questions to learn new words (45-75 minutes)!
Answer.Comments:
This was an excruciatingly boring and repetitive way to earn one hundred and fifty cents, on the assumption that I did (my mTurkdom was not on the exclusion list, even though I took a similar study; something I only ealized after the survey commenced; I completed it in good faith).  Surely you can go about confirming or testing your hypothethis in a less mental carpal tunnel syndrome-inducing mechanical  fashion.  Please.  The guys at ETH Zurich make theirs potentially repetitive tasks a pleasure to work on.  Why don't you learn something from them, pretty please.

Respectfully,
Marek Lugowski
Chicago
